pull_request.title: fix: Fix types of Range class fields.
pull_request.body:
Documentation states that it should be `string`.
https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/tables#RangePartitioning However testing REST requests with real instance show that it's `int`. Also it can be tested here by tryng to create a valid json https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/jobs/insert

https://screenshot.googleplex.com/SLnKvpUu3uSsv6Q
https://screenshot.googleplex.com/866oUQfjCRmHmC7

pull_request.title: fix: Do not use `output only` fields in `input` json payload.
pull_request.body:
Some of those fields are objects which contain fields, required by BQ API. Even if it's not used by it. Documentation states that these fields are `output only`, which should be save enough to remove it from serialization process (`to_json` function).

https://cloud.google.com/bigquery/docs/reference/rest/v2/Job

pull_request.title: fix: Use default values
pull_request.body:
Default values of these fields are empty strings.
BQ API doesn't accept empty strings, according to documentation these fields are enums.
`location` is not enum according to documentation, but it works similar - only valid location is accepted.
